{"kind":"FETCH","data":{"headers":{},"body":"{\"id\":58870096,\"title\":\"Best Places to Have a Dog Birthday Party\",\"slug\":\"best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party\",\"excerpt\":\"Planning a dog birthday party? Discover the best venues in 2026 from indoor dog parks to dog-friendly breweries. Complete guide with costs, planning tips, and venue comparison.\",\"content\":\"<h2>Why Dog Birthday Parties Have Gone Mainstream</h2>\\n<p>Gone are the days when throwing a birthday party for your dog seemed over the top. Today, celebrating your pup's special day is a beloved tradition for millions of dog owners—and a rapidly growing segment of the <strong>$136.8 billion</strong> pet industry.</p>\\n<p>According to a 2024 survey by the <a href=\\\"https://www.americanpetproducts.org/\\\">American Pet Products Association (APPA)</a>, <strong>76% of dog owners consider their pets family members</strong>, and nearly <strong>40% celebrate their dog's birthday</strong> in some way. That's over 30 million dog birthday celebrations happening across America each year.</p>\\n<p>But here's the question every pet parent eventually asks: <strong>where should I host my dog's party?</strong></p>\\n<p>After planning over 200 dog birthday events in my decade as a pet event coordinator, I've seen everything from backyard barbecues to elaborate venue parties. In this guide, I'll walk you through the <strong>best venues for dog birthday parties</strong>—from budget-friendly options to premium experiences.</p>\\n<h2>Top Venue Types for Dog Birthday Parties</h2>\\n<h3>Quick Comparison</h3>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<th>Venue Type</th>\\n<th>Average Cost</th>\\n<th>Party Size</th>\\n<th>Best For</th>\\n<th>Weather-Proof</th>\\n</tr>\\n</thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Indoor Dog Parks</td>\\n<td>$50-$200</td>\\n<td>5-15 dogs</td>\\n<td>Active dogs, year-round parties</td>\\n<td>✓ Yes</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Doggy Soft Play</td>\\n<td>$75-$250</td>\\n<td>5-10 dogs</td>\\n<td>Puppies, small breeds</td>\\n<td>✓ Yes</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Dog-Friendly Breweries</td>\\n<td>$0-$100</td>\\n<td>5-20 dogs</td>\\n<td>Adult owners, casual vibes</td>\\n<td>✗ Varies</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Private Party Rentals</td>\\n<td>$100-$400</td>\\n<td>10-30 dogs</td>\\n<td>Large groups, exclusive access</td>\\n<td>✓ Yes</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Dog Daycare Facilities</td>\\n<td>$50-$150</td>\\n<td>5-15 dogs</td>\\n<td>Regular daycare clients</td>\\n<td>✓ Yes</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Public Dog Parks</td>\\n<td>Free</td>\\n<td>Unlimited</td>\\n<td>Budget parties, socialized dogs</td>\\n<td>✗ No</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Your Backyard</td>\\n<td>$0-$50</td>\\n<td>2-10 dogs</td>\\n<td>Small groups, familiar dogs</td>\\n<td>✗ No</td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>\\n\\n<h2>1. Indoor Dog Parks: The Premium Party Choice</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $50-$200 for private party packages <strong>Best For:</strong> Active dogs, year-round celebrations, climate-controlled fun</p>\\n<p>Indoor dog parks have become the go-to venue for dog birthday parties, and for good reason. These <a href=\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\">climate-controlled facilities</a> offer everything dog parties need: safe play areas, professional supervision, and protection from weather surprises.</p>\\n<h3>Why Indoor Dog Parks Excel for Parties</h3>\\n<p><strong>Climate Control Matters More Than You Think</strong></p>\\n<p>I once planned an outdoor August party in Phoenix where temperatures hit 105°F. Half the dogs spent the entire time panting under shade tents. Since then, I always recommend <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/parks\\\">indoor facilities</a> for any party during extreme weather seasons.</p>\\n<p>According to the <a href=\\\"https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/health/heat-stroke-in-dogs/\\\">American Kennel Club</a>, dogs can suffer heat stroke in temperatures as low as 80°F—especially brachycephalic breeds like Bulldogs and Pugs. Indoor facilities maintain comfortable 65-75°F temperatures year-round.</p>\\n<p><strong>Built for Dogs, By Design</strong></p>\\n<p>The best indoor parks feature:</p>\\n<ul><li><strong>Rubberized or padded flooring</strong> (gentle on joints, easy to clean)</li><li><strong>Separate play areas</strong> by size and energy level</li><li><strong>Professional staff</strong> trained in canine behavior</li><li><strong>Easy cleanup</strong> for inevitable accidents</li></ul>\\n<h3>Top Features to Look for in Indoor Party Venues</h3>\\n<p>✓ Private party room or exclusive booking options ✓ Staff supervision during play ✓ Flexible time slots (1-3 hours typical) ✓ Space for cake cutting and photos ✓ Ability to bring outside food and treats ✓ Proof of vaccination required (safety first)</p>\\n<h3>What Indoor Dog Park Parties Usually Include</h3>\\n<p>Most facilities offer party packages that include:</p>\\n<ul><li>1-2 hours of exclusive or semi-private play time</li><li>Staff supervision</li><li>Tables and seating for humans</li><li>Basic decorations (or permission to bring your own)</li><li>Water stations for dogs</li></ul>\\n<p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Ask about weekday discounts. Many indoor parks offer <strong>20-30% off</strong> for Monday-Thursday party bookings.</p>\\n<p>Find <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org\\\">indoor dog parks near you</a> that offer party hosting.</p>\\n<h2>2. Doggy Soft Play Facilities: Perfect for Puppies and Small Breeds</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $75-$250 for party packages <strong>Best For:</strong> Puppies, senior dogs, small breeds, anxious dogs</p>\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/top-10-doggy-soft-play-areas-los-angeles\\\">Doggy soft play facilities</a> take indoor parties to another level with padded flooring, obstacle courses, and lower-impact play environments. If your birthday pup is a puppy under a year old or a small breed that gets overwhelmed by larger dogs, soft play is the ideal choice.</p>\\n<h3>What Makes Soft Play Different</h3>\\n<p><strong>Padded Environment = Safer Play</strong></p>\\n<p>Soft play facilities use 4-6 inches of impact-absorbing padding throughout play areas. This matters especially for:</p>\\n<ul><li><strong>Puppies</strong> with developing joints</li><li><strong>Senior dogs</strong> with arthritis or mobility issues</li><li><strong>Small breeds</strong> who can be accidentally injured during rough play</li><li><strong>Recovering dogs</strong> post-surgery or injury</li></ul>\\n<p><strong>Size-Appropriate Socialization</strong></p>\\n<p>Most soft play venues maintain strict size separation—meaning your Chihuahua won't be sharing space with a Great Dane. This creates a safer, less intimidating party environment.</p>\\n<h3>Typical Soft Play Party Packages</h3>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<th>Package Level</th>\\n<th>Price Range</th>\\n<th>Includes</th>\\n</tr>\\n</thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Basic</td>\\n<td>$75-$100</td>\\n<td>1 hour play, 5-8 dogs, minimal decorations</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Standard</td>\\n<td>$125-$175</td>\\n<td>1.5 hours, 8-10 dogs, decorations, cake time</td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Premium</td>\\n<td>$200-$250</td>\\n<td>2 hours, 10-12 dogs, photos, goodie bags</td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>\\n<h2>3. Dog-Friendly Breweries and Restaurants: Party for Humans and Hounds</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $0-$100 (food/drink purchases) <strong>Best For:</strong> Social owners, adult-focused gatherings, casual vibes</p>\\n<p>The rise of <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/parks-with-bars\\\">dog-friendly bars and breweries</a> has created a unique party option: venues where humans can enjoy craft beers and great food while their dogs socialize in designated dog areas.</p>\\n<h3>The Appeal of Brewery Parties</h3>\\n<p><strong>It's Fun for Humans Too</strong></p>\\n<figure class=\\\"video-figure\\\"><div class=\\\"video-wrapper video-youtube\\\"><iframe src=\\\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/CeEFE-zmwu4?rel=0&autoplay=0&loop=0\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allow=\\\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\\\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><figcaption> Dog birthday celebration videos Compilation | Happy Pets Birthday | Must Watch</figcaption></figure>\\n<p>Let's be honest: some dog birthday parties are as much about the humans connecting as the dogs playing. Brewery venues let pet parents relax, enjoy quality drinks, and celebrate without the stress of hosting at home.</p>\\n<p><strong>Lower Coordination Requirements</strong></p>\\n<p>Unlike dedicated dog party venues, breweries typically don't require deposits, contracts, or minimum headcounts. You simply reserve a large table (or outdoor section), invite guests, and let the party unfold organically.</p>\\n<h3>Top Dog-Friendly Brewery Chains</h3>\\n<ul><li><strong>Lazy Dog Restaurant & Bar</strong> – Indoor/outdoor dog-friendly with dog menus in most locations</li><li><strong>Three Dog Bakery</strong> – Specializes in dog treats and party hosting</li><li><strong>Local craft breweries</strong> – Many have expanded outdoor patios with dog areas</li></ul>\\n<h3>Things to Consider</h3>\\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Not all dogs suit brewery environments.</strong> Busy patios with strangers, other dogs, and sensory overload can overwhelm anxious or reactive pups.</p>\\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Weather-dependent.</strong> Most dog-friendly brewery spaces are outdoors.</p>\\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Limited dog supervision.</strong> You're responsible for monitoring your dog's behavior.</p>\\n<h2>4. Private Dog Park Rentals: Exclusive Access</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $100-$400 for 2-3 hours <strong>Best For:</strong> Large parties, dogs needing space, premium experiences</p>\\n<p>Some facilities offer exclusive private rentals—meaning you get the entire property to yourself for a set time window. This is perfect for:</p>\\n<ul><li><strong>Large groups</strong> (15+ dogs)</li><li><strong>Dogs with selective social preferences</strong></li><li><strong>Special needs dogs</strong> who need controlled environments</li><li><strong>Owners wanting a premium, stress-free experience</strong></li></ul>\\n<h3>What Private Rentals Include</h3>\\n<p>Most private rentals offer:</p>\\n<ul><li>2-3 hours of exclusive access</li><li>Full use of play areas, equipment, and facilities</li><li>Staff on-site for safety</li><li>Freedom to bring decorations, food, photographers</li><li>Flexible scheduling (including evenings and weekends)</li></ul>\\n<h3>Where to Find Private Rentals</h3>\\n<ul><li><strong>Dedicated indoor dog parks</strong> – Many offer off-hours exclusive bookings</li><li><strong>Dog training facilities</strong> – Often rent space during non-class hours</li><li><strong>Agility centers</strong> – Great for active dogs who love obstacles</li><li><strong>Doggy daycares</strong> – May offer after-hours private parties</li></ul>\\n<p>Search our <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org\\\">indoor dog park directory</a> and filter for facilities offering private party options.</p>\\n<h2>5. Dog Daycare Facilities: Party Where They're Already Comfortable</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $50-$150 <strong>Best For:</strong> Regular daycare clients, easy planning</p>\\n<p>If your dog already attends daycare, hosting a party there has significant advantages: your pup is already comfortable in the environment, staff knows their personality, and fellow daycare dogs make natural party guests.</p>\\n<h3>Benefits of Daycare Parties</h3>\\n<p>✓ <strong>Familiar environment</strong> reduces birthday pup's stress ✓ <strong>Built-in guest list</strong> from regular playmates ✓ <strong>Staff expertise</strong> in managing group play ✓ <strong>Established trust</strong> with the facility and team</p>\\n<h3>Typical Daycare Party Options</h3>\\n<p>Many daycares offer simple add-on party services:</p>\\n<ul><li><strong>Cake and photo session:</strong> $25-$50</li><li><strong>Mini party (30-45 min):</strong> $50-$75</li><li><strong>Full party package:</strong> $100-$150</li></ul>\\n<p>Ask your regular daycare about their party options—many facilities offer discounts for established clients.</p>\\n<h2>6. Public Dog Parks: The Free Option</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> Free <strong>Best For:</strong> Budget parties, well-socialized dogs, casual gatherings</p>\\n<p>Public off-leash dog parks offer a free venue, but they come with significant trade-offs. I generally only recommend public park parties for:</p>\\n<ul><li><strong>Extremely well-socialized dogs</strong> comfortable with stranger dogs</li><li><strong>Owners with limited budgets</strong></li><li><strong>Small, low-key celebrations</strong> (just cake and photos)</li></ul>\\n<h3>The Reality Check</h3>\\n<p><strong>You have zero control over the environment.</strong></p>\\n<p>Anyone can enter a public dog park at any time. This means:</p>\\n<ul><li>Unknown dogs with unknown temperaments</li><li>No vaccination verification</li><li>No staff to intervene in conflicts</li><li>No reservation or guaranteed space</li></ul>\\n<p><strong>My Honest Recommendation:</strong> If you're inviting guests, skip public parks. The liability and stress aren't worth the cost savings.</p>\\n<h2>7. Your Backyard: The DIY Classic</h2>\\n<p><strong>Cost:</strong> $0-$100 (decorations, cake, supplies) <strong>Best For:</strong> Small groups, dogs that know each other, budget-conscious owners</p>\\n<p>Home parties remain the most popular option for intimate gatherings. With a secure, fenced yard and a guest list of familiar dogs, backyard parties can be wonderful.</p>\\n<h3>Making Home Parties Work</h3>\\n<p><strong>Essential Requirements:</strong></p>\\n<ul><li>Secure fencing (no escape routes)</li><li>Clean-up supplies ready</li><li>Shade and water stations</li><li>Separate space for dogs who need breaks</li><li>First aid kit accessible</li></ul>\\n<p><strong>The Guest List Matters Most</strong></p>\\n<p>Only invite dogs that already know and get along with each other. Introducing new dogs at a party is a recipe for conflict and stress.</p>\\n<h2>Dog Birthday Party Planning Checklist</h2>\\n<h3>4 Weeks Before</h3>\\n<ul><li>Choose venue and book reservation</li><li>Create guest list (dogs AND humans)</li><li>Send invitations with vaccine requirements</li><li>Order or plan custom cake</li></ul>\\n<h3>1 Week Before</h3>\\n<ul><li>Confirm RSVPs and headcount</li><li>Purchase decorations and supplies</li><li>Plan activities and photo opportunities</li><li>Prepare goodie bags for guests</li></ul>\\n<h3>Day Of</h3>\\n<ul><li>Arrive early to set up</li><li>Brief venue staff on any special needs</li><li>Monitor dog energy levels throughout</li><li>Capture photos and videos</li><li>Have cleanup supplies ready</li></ul>\\n<h2>Budget Breakdown: What Dog Parties Actually Cost</h2>\\n<p>Based on my experience planning events and industry data, here's what to expect:</p>\\n<h3>Budget Party ($50-$100)</h3>\\n<ul><li>Public park or backyard venue: $0</li><li>Simple dog cake: $25-$40</li><li>Basic decorations: $15-$25</li><li>Goodie bags: $10-$20</li></ul>\\n<h3>Mid-Range Party ($150-$250)</h3>\\n<ul><li>Indoor dog park rental: $75-$150</li><li>Custom dog cake: $40-$60</li><li>Decorations and supplies: $30-$50</li><li>Photo session or professional pics: $50-$100</li></ul>\\n<h3>Premium Party ($300-$500+)</h3>\\n<ul><li>Private facility rental: $150-$300</li><li>Professional cake and treats: $75-$125</li><li>Full decoration setup: $50-$100</li><li>Professional photographer: $100-$200</li><li>Goodie bags with premium items: $50-$75</li></ul>\\n<h2>Finding the Right Venue: Questions to Ask</h2>\\n<p>Before booking any venue, ask these essential questions:</p>\\n<ol><li><strong>What's included in the party package?</strong></li><li><strong>Is there a separate party space, or is it shared with regular guests?</strong></li><li><strong>What are your vaccine requirements?</strong></li><li><strong>Do you allow outside food and treats?</strong></li><li><strong>Is there staff supervision during the party?</strong></li><li><strong>What's your cancellation policy?</strong></li><li><strong>Do you have experience with dog parties?</strong></li><li><strong>Are there any breed restrictions?</strong></li></ol>\\n<h2>Safety Tips for Dog Birthday Parties</h2>\\n<h3>Food Safety</h3>\\n<ul><li>Use dog-safe cake recipes (no chocolate, xylitol, or grapes)</li><li>Keep human food out of dog reach</li><li>Monitor treat distribution to prevent overfeeding</li><li>Have water stations readily available</li></ul>\\n<h3>Behavioral Safety</h3>\\n<ul><li>Never force dogs to interact</li><li>Provide quiet break areas for overwhelmed pups</li><li>Watch for stress signals (yawning, lip licking, whale eye)</li><li>Have a plan for separating dogs if conflicts arise</li></ul>\\n<h3>Health Safety</h3>\\n<ul><li>Require proof of current vaccinations</li><li>Have a first aid kit accessible</li><li>Know the location of the nearest emergency vet</li><li>Keep a list of guest owners' contact information</li></ul>\\n<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\\n<h3>How many dogs should I invite to a birthday party?</h3>\\n<p>Keep it manageable: <strong>5-10 dogs</strong> is ideal for most venues. Quality over quantity—a smaller group of dogs that know each other creates a better experience than a large group of strangers.</p>\\n<h3>What age should my dog be for a birthday party?</h3>\\n<p>Dogs as young as <strong>4-6 months</strong> (after completing initial vaccinations) can enjoy parties. For puppies, choose <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/top-10-doggy-soft-play-areas-los-angeles\\\">soft play venues</a> with age-appropriate environments.</p>\\n<h3>Are dog birthday cakes safe?</h3>\\n<p>Cakes made specifically for dogs are safe when they avoid toxic ingredients (chocolate, xylitol, grapes, raisins). Popular dog-safe ingredients include:</p>\\n<ul><li>Peanut butter (xylitol-free)</li><li>Pumpkin puree</li><li>Banana</li><li>Carrot</li><li>Plain yogurt</li></ul>\\n<h3>Should I require vaccinations for guest dogs?</h3>\\n<p><strong>Absolutely yes.</strong> Require proof of:</p>\\n<ul><li>Rabies (required by law)</li><li>DHPP (Distemper, Hepatitis, Parvo, Parainfluenza)</li><li>Bordetella (kennel cough) – especially for indoor venues</li></ul>\\n<h3>What if my dog gets overwhelmed during the party?</h3>\\n<p>Have an exit plan. Bring a crate, carrier, or designate a quiet room where your pup can decompress. Watch for stress signals and be ready to give breaks as needed.</p>\\n<h2>Conclusion: Find the Perfect Venue for Your Pup's Big Day</h2>\\n<p>Your dog's birthday party should be a joyful celebration—for both your pup and you. The right venue makes all the difference between a stressful event and a wonderful memory.</p>\\n<p><strong>My top recommendations:</strong></p>\\n<ul><li><strong>For most dogs:</strong> <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org\\\">Indoor dog parks</a> offer the best balance of safety, convenience, and fun</li><li><strong>For puppies and small breeds:</strong> <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/top-10-doggy-soft-play-areas-los-angeles\\\">Soft play facilities</a> with padded environments</li><li><strong>For social owners:</strong> Dog-friendly breweries combine human and canine celebration</li><li><strong>For intimate gatherings:</strong> Your backyard with familiar doggy friends</li></ul>\\n<p>Whatever venue you choose, the most important ingredient is love. Your dog doesn't care about elaborate decorations—they care about the people (and pups) who celebrate with them.</p>\\n<p><strong>Ready to start planning?</strong> Browse our <a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org\\\">indoor dog park directory</a> to find party-friendly venues near you.</p>\\n<h2>Sources & Citations</h2>\\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\\n<ul><li><a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/top-10-doggy-soft-play-areas-los-angeles\\\">Top 10 Doggy Soft Play Areas in Los Angeles</a></li><li><a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/best-indoor-dog-parks-new-york-city\\\">Best Indoor Dog Parks in New York City</a></li><li><a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/why-arent-there-more-indoor-dog-parks\\\">Why Aren't There More Indoor Dog Parks?</a></li><li><a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/blog/how-much-is-puppy-obedience-training\\\">How Much Is Puppy Obedience Training?</a></li><li><a href=\\\"https://indoordogpark.org/parks-with-bars\\\">Find Dog Parks with Bars Near You</a></li></ul>\\n<h3>Footnotes</h3>\\n<ol><li><em>American Pet Products Association. (2024). \\\"2024-2025 APPA National Pet Owners Survey.\\\" </em><a href=\\\"https://www.americanpetproducts.org/\\\"><em>https://www.americanpetproducts.org/</em></a><em> </em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/mahendrabalal/new_indoordogpark/new/main?filename=README.md#user-content-fnref-1-e0baaa02214223b21c60cdf049c56dd2\\\"><em>↩</em></a></li><li><em>APPA. (2024). \\\"Pet Ownership & Demographics Sourcebook.\\\" American Pet Products Association. </em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/mahendrabalal/new_indoordogpark/new/main?filename=README.md#user-content-fnref-2-e0baaa02214223b21c60cdf049c56dd2\\\"><em>↩</em></a></li><li><em>American Kennel Club. (2024). \\\"Heat Stroke in Dogs: Symptoms, Treatment, and Prevention.\\\" </em><a href=\\\"https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/health/heat-stroke-in-dogs/\\\"><em>https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/health/heat-stroke-in-dogs/</em></a><em> </em><a href=\\\"https://github.com/mahendrabalal/new_indoordogpark/new/main?filename=README.md#user-content-fnref-3-e0baaa02214223b21c60cdf049c56dd2\\\"><em>↩</em></a></li></ol>\",\"date\":\"2025-12-28T00:03:21.485Z\",\"modified\":\"2025-12-28T16:45:39Z\",\"author\":{\"id\":3894619,\"name\":\"Mahendra Balal\",\"slug\":\"article\",\"description\":\"Mahendra is a professional pet-specific content writer.\",\"url\":\"\",\"link\":\"/blog/author/article\",\"avatar_urls\":{\"24\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/fe569ca7a7aea456e6d846511889756220b0ff98-1029x579.jpg?rect=226,0,579,579&w=24&h=24\",\"48\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/fe569ca7a7aea456e6d846511889756220b0ff98-1029x579.jpg?rect=226,0,579,579&w=48&h=48\",\"96\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/fe569ca7a7aea456e6d846511889756220b0ff98-1029x579.jpg?rect=226,0,579,579&w=96&h=96\"}},\"categories\":[{\"id\":5323753,\"name\":\"Dog Daycare\",\"slug\":\"dog-daycare\",\"description\":\"\",\"count\":0,\"link\":\"/blog/category/dog-daycare\",\"taxonomy\":\"category\",\"parent\":0,\"meta\":{}}],\"tags\":[{\"id\":90100489,\"name\":\"Pets care\",\"slug\":\"pets-care\",\"description\":\"\",\"count\":0,\"link\":\"/blog/tag/pets-care\",\"taxonomy\":\"post_tag\",\"meta\":{}}],\"featuredImage\":{\"id\":64176558,\"date\":\"2025-12-28T00:03:21.485Z\",\"slug\":\"best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party\",\"type\":\"attachment\",\"link\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/6a41d7b6558c765ae4a67906727a2f707a3a216b-1024x1024.webp\",\"title\":{\"rendered\":\"dog-birthday\"},\"author\":3894619,\"caption\":{\"rendered\":\"Three dogs in birthday events \"},\"alt_text\":\"dog-birthday\",\"media_type\":\"image\",\"mime_type\":\"image/jpeg\",\"media_details\":{\"width\":1024,\"height\":1024,\"file\":\"best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party.jpg\",\"sizes\":{\"large\":{\"file\":\"best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party-large.jpg\",\"width\":1200,\"height\":1200,\"mime_type\":\"image/jpeg\",\"source_url\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/6a41d7b6558c765ae4a67906727a2f707a3a216b-1024x1024.webp?w=1200\"},\"medium\":{\"file\":\"best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party-medium.jpg\",\"width\":800,\"height\":800,\"mime_type\":\"image/jpeg\",\"source_url\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/6a41d7b6558c765ae4a67906727a2f707a3a216b-1024x1024.webp?w=800\"}}},\"source_url\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ruuprk8g/production/6a41d7b6558c765ae4a67906727a2f707a3a216b-1024x1024.webp?w=1200\"},\"link\":\"/blog/best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party\",\"status\":\"publish\",\"commentStatus\":\"open\"}","status":200,"url":""},"revalidate":300,"tags":["blog-posts","blog-post-best-places-to-have-a-dog-birthday-party"]}